commitResults.messageTitle: Improve Code Quality by Enhancing Readability and Structure
commitResults.messageBody:
Extracted methods to reduce the size of previously existing methods, making them more manageable and focused on a single responsibility.
Removed unused variables and methods, streamlining the code and improving clarity.
Applied KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid) principles to simplify complex code, making it easier to understand and maintain.
Reorganized code logically to enhance readability and flow, ensuring a more intuitive structure.
Utilized the default branch for code consistency and ease of management.
Avoided recycling variables and parameters to prevent unintended side effects and increase code clarity.
Removed empty catch blocks to handle exceptions properly and avoid silent failures.
Deleted dead code to eliminate unnecessary clutter and improve performance.
Added comments to clarify the purpose and functionality of code sections, aiding in understanding and future maintenance.

These changes collectively enhance the overall quality of the code, making it more readable, maintainable, and robust.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor findTasks Method to use Streams
commitResults.messageBody:
Replaced Iteration with Streams: Updated the findTasks method in the TaskList class to utilize Java Streams for more concise and expressive filtering.

Filtering Logic: Leveraged Stream API's filter method to search for tasks with descriptions that contain the specified search term, ignoring case.

Result Collection: Collected the filtered results into a List<Task> and converted it back to an ArrayList<Task> for compatibility with existing code.

Edge Case Handling: Ensured that if the provided description is null or empty, the method returns an empty ArrayList to handle such scenarios gracefully.
